text=Wanton Wicked Logo%0aWanton Wicked Logo%0aForums%0aUtilities%0aPlots%0aScenes%0aPlayer Utilities%0aDashboard%0aCreate a Character%0aRequests%0aPlay Preferences%0aView Other Character%0aHelp%0aMeet the Team%0aTerms of Use%0aCode of Conduct%0aSite Policies%0aHouse Rules%0aNew Player Help%0aGuides%0aWiki Guide%0aChat Help%0aRequest System%0aExperience Guide%0aSanctioning Guide%0aCharacter Creation%0aThe City%0aSetting Introduction%0aThe Embassy%0aSpheres%0aMap%0aThe Districts%0aCast List%0aThe Venues%0aChangeling%0aAbout the Venue%0aChangeling Player Guide%0aChangeling Forums%0aChangeling Cast List%0aFae-Touched Cast List%0aMage%0aAbout the Venue%0aMage Player Guide%0aMage Forums%0aMage Cast List%0aMortal/+%0aAbout the Venue%0aMortal/+ Player Guide%0aMortal/+ Forums%0aMortal/+ Cast List%0aVampire%0aAbout the Venue%0aVampire Player Guide%0aVampire Forums%0aVampire Cast List%0aGhoul Cast List%0aWerewolf%0aAbout the Venue%0aWerewolf Player Guide%0aWerewolf Forums%0aWerewolf Cast List%0aWolfblooded Cast List%0aGoogle [Bot]%0aUser Control Panel%0aLogout%0aGo%0aGameRef: Character Creation%0aContents (hide)%0a%0aBook Policy%0aGuidelines for All Characters%0a“Z-Splats”%0aCharacter Demographics and Background%0aAffiliations%0aBiography and Notes%0aStats%0aAttributes%0aSkills%0aTraits%0aAbilities%0aMerits%0aInfluences%0aAnchors%0aAspirations%0aIntegrity and equivalents%0aEquipment%0aSanctioning%0aHouse Rules%0aThis guide has been created to lead you through creating a character for Chronicles of Darkness: Portland, OR. This guide applies to all characters, however, there are venue specific character creation rules cited throughout. Half-template (Fae-touched, Ghouls and Wolf-Blooded) character creation rules are addressed under their parent venues.%0a%0aBook Policy%0aSee Book Policy for approved resources.%0a%0aGuidelines for All Characters%0aChronicle%0aSelect: Portland, OR%0aAge%0aAll characters must be (and appear to be) 18 years or older. See Site Policies And Practices.%0aFree Bonuses%0aCertain traits (abilities, merits, etc.) grant additional bonuses elsewhere such as a bonus specialty or +1 to an attribute. If your character is granted a bonus, make note of it in your NOTES section of the character sheet. During sanctioning, the staff member will use that list to update your character sheet. Example: Professional Training merit grants free Contact merit.%0a“Z-Splats”%0aBecause of uneven and limited publication of “Z-splat” content (Legacies, Bloodlines, etc.), these are not currently available to any characters.%0a%0aCharacter Demographics and Background%0aName%0aEnter the character’s name.%0aFor ease of use, it is a best practice to use standard alphanumeric characters.%0aNicknames: If a character is generally referred to by a nickname instead of their first name, enter the nickname for the first name.%0aAlternate Identity: If a character has an Alternate Identity they go by publicly that is different from their actual name, use that. (i.e., James Cooper goes by Johnathan Tucker as he’s in witness protection)%0aMage Only	%0aShadow Name%0aThe Shadow Name should be entered in hyphens between the first and last name: John -Sparklepants- Smith%0aWerewolves Only	%0aDeed Name%0aThe Deed Name should be entered in hyphens between the first and last name: Jane -Dances With Humans- Doe%0aAge%0aIf it varies, enter the character’s apparent age and then their actual age parenthetically. As in: 25 (50)%0a%0a[[#top | &#8593; back to top]]%0a%0aAffiliations%0aThis area contains unique fields for each Character Type. Use the Drop Downs to select. Below are listed some specific explanations.%0a%0aChangeling Only	%0aFetch%0aEnter the Fetch’s name. Additional information will be required in the Biography.%0aGhoul Only	%0aGhoul%0aUse the applicable Drop Down to select the applicable Clan of your character’s Regnant.%0aGhoul%0aEnter the Regnant’s name. Additional information will be required in the Biography.%0a%0a[[#top | &#8593; back to top]]%0a%0aBiography and Notes%0aCompose a biography that identifies in written form or bullet point the history of your character that addresses the following:%0a%0aSignificant events or overall experience in childhood or adolescence%0aSignificant events or overall experience in adulthood (relationships, professions, traumas, successes, etc.)%0aSignificant events or experiences which lead towards the character obtaining specialized merits (professional training, contacts, allies, etc.), abilities or statistics. Items which require this will be noted in this guide.%0aIf applicable, when the character moved to Portland including any significant events or motivations around the move.%0aIf you compose a biography which is more than 5–7 paragraphs, you must also include a bullet pointed summary of all key points.%0a%0aSupernatural Only	%0aEvents surrounding becoming a supernatural character (awakening, first change, etc.)%0aSignificant events or overall experience after becoming a supernatural character (joining covenant, tribe, coterie, etc.)%0aMortal/+ Only	%0aIf applicable, events surrounding becoming aware of the supernatural including which factions or spheres they are currently aware of%0aSignificant events or overall experience after becoming aware of the supernatural%0aIf applicable, events surrounding joining any groups or becoming associated with particular Factions.%0aBanned Backgrounds/Concepts%0aPlease be aware that the following backgrounds or concepts are not allowed:%0a%0aAnachronistic or over-the-top concepts. (Ninja, serial killer, Queen of England)%0aRecreations of signature characters of any book, film or other popular fiction.%0aDirect recreation of any actual person, living or dead.%0aCharacters already played by you or another person during WW5 or currently on another site. See Site Policies And Practices.%0aAntagonist concepts (Loyalists, Pure, Seers, etc.)%0aBackgrounds which include rape. See Site Policy.%0aNotes%0aThis field is primarily to call out any bonus items gained from the purchase of other traits. Sanctioning staff members will use this section to complete your character sheet during sanctioning.%0a%0a[[#top | &#8593; back to top]]%0a%0aStats%0aAttributes%0aUnlike the RAW Character Creation, we do not limit Attribute point allocation at Character Creation to 5/4/3. All Attributes begin at 1 for free.%0a%0aAttribute 4+%0aThis must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0aAttribute 1%0aThis must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0aSkills%0aUnlike the RAW Character Creation, we do not limit Skill point allocation at Character Creation to 11/7/4.%0a%0aSkill 4+%0aThis must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0aOccult Specialties%0aThis must be explained in Biography or Notes. Specialties in other Character Types represents significant “insider” knowledge and requires a detailed and fitting explanation.%0a%0a[[#top | &#8593; back to top]]%0a%0aTraits%0aNOTE%0aCertain traits (abilities, merits, etc.) grant additional bonuses elsewhere such as a bonus specialty or +1 to an attribute. If your character is granted a bonus, make note of it in your NOTES section of the character sheet. During sanctioning, the staff member will use that list to update your character sheet. Example: Professional Training.%0aAbilities%0aAll	%0aCost Breaks%0aMerits and powers providing Experience cost breaks do not apply to character creation unless they explicitly say so.%0a%0aChangeling Only	%0aWyrd%0a3 must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a4+ is not allowed at Character Creation.%0aPledges%0aThis must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0aNon-Affinity Abilities%0aCheck the “NA” box for all Non-Affinity Contracts.%0aMage Only	%0aGnosis%0a3 must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a4+ is not allowed at Character Creation.%0aPraxis%0aRemember to record a number of free Praxes equal to the character’s Gnosis in Notes to be added to the sheet during sanctioning%0aArcana%0a4+ is not allowed at Character Creation.%0aVampire Only	%0aBlood Potency%0a3 must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a4+ is not allowed at Character Creation.%0aNon-Affinity Abilities%0aCheck the “NA” box for all Non-Affinity Disciplines.%0aWerewolf Only	%0aPrimal Urge%0a3 must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a4+ is not allowed at Character Creation.%0aNon-Affinity Abilities%0aCheck the “NA” box for all Non-Affinity Gifts.%0aWolf-Blooded Only	%0aTells%0aTells are capped at 4 total at creation, with those after the first purchased as a merit normally.%0aThe following Tells are only available at Character Creation as they are Tells present from birth:%0aMoon Marked%0aSecond Skin%0aShadow Twin%0a%0a[[#top | &#8593; back to top]]%0a%0aMerits%0aAll Merit purchases at Character Creation must meet the Prerequisites in the RAW. The following general Merit guidelines are applicable to all merits except where listed under the specific Merit type.%0a%0aMerit 4+%0aThis must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0aScaled Merit 4+ without a listed pre-requisite%0aLimited to 2 at Character Creation.%0aMortal Only	Per Hurt Locker, the following minor templates are available:%0aAtariya%0aPlain%0aLost Boys%0aPsychic Vampires%0aThe first dot in the defining merit of the minor template is free.%0a%0aSupernatural Merits	Ghouls, Wolf-Blooded and Fae-Touched are not eligible for Supernatural Merits listed in Chronicles of Darkness.%0aWolf-Blooded Only	%0aRaised By Wolves%0aThis merit is required for a character who is a part of one of the Families. Being part of a Family is not a prerequisite for taking the merit if the character was raised among other werewolves.%0a%0a[[#top | &#8593; back to top]]%0a%0aMental Merits%0aProfessional Training 2+%0aLimited to 1 at Character Creation.%0aUse the Notes section under Character Bio to identify the merit or skill benefits obtained by this merit, and the Sanctioning Staff will add them to your sheet during sanctioning.%0aSelect two applicable Asset Skills if your Profession is not listed in the RAW, and there is not a close approximation.%0aSocial Merits%0aAllies, Contacts, Mentor%0aThis must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0aIn the Merit Notes include the Sphere which the Allies, Contact or Mentor represents. As in: Contacts: (City Hall/Government) Mayor’s Office%0aMystery Cult Initiation%0aA character may only have a total of 5 6 dots assigned to this merit(s). This must be explained in Biography or Notes.+}%0aInitiation may be in a setting-created Cults or Groups (See ) or a player may create a new Cult. However, player-created Cults become part of the setting upon approval and may be co-opted into a primary setting cult and/or utilized for plot.%0aPlayer-created Cults must be detailed in the Notes including an overview, cultist archetypes and rewards for each dot tier per the RAW guidelines. (CoD p.52)%0aUse the Notes section under Character Bio to identify the merit or skill benefits obtained by this merit, and the Sanctioning Staff will add them to your sheet during sanctioning.%0aNeighborhood 1+%0aThis is a House Ruled Merit. This must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0aNeighborhood 3+ not allowed as an individual purchase at Character Creation.%0aResources 3+%0aThis must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0aSafe Place 3+%0aThis must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0aStatus%0aThis merit can only be purchased up to 2. All characters receive 1 free dot of status in one Faction-specific group (for example, a vampire may take 1 free dot of either Covenant or Clan status).%0aThe following Spheres are available for purchasing status:%0aArts and Society%0aBusiness%0aCrime%0aEducation%0aLaw and Order%0aMedia%0aMedical%0aShadow Status in this Sphere cannot be purchased at Character Creation.%0aPhysical Merits%0aFighting Style 3+%0aLimited to 1 at Character Creation.%0a%0a[[#top | &#8593; back to top]]%0a%0aInfluences%0aAnchors%0aFor Virtue and Vice, Masque and Mein, Mask and Dirge, or Blood and Bone select the applicable choice from the Drop Down or enter a custom value.%0a%0aTouchstone%0aFor supernatural characters, this must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0aAspirations%0aSee Site Policies And Practices for Aspirations help.%0a%0aShort Term Aspiration%0aChoose at least two short-term aspirations.%0aLong term Aspiration%0aChoose at least one long-term aspiration.%0aMage Only	%0aObsessions%0aChoose at least one long-term obsession that is associated with your mystical life.%0aIntegrity and equivalents%0aMortal Only	%0aQuestionaire%0aThese questions need to be answered in addition to the Biography and Notes.%0aFor applicable characters	%0aIdentify Breaking Points%0a%0aNote:	%0aYou never have to make breaking point/detachment/etc rolls for things that happened before sanctioning (for example, a Vampire that has Cruac).%0a%0a[[#top | &#8593; back to top]]%0a%0aEquipment%0aAdd any equipment plus applicable modifiers to your character sheet.%0a%0aCost 1–3%0aSome leeway is given for one Cost 3 item, 2 Cost 2 items or 3 Cost 1 items without adequate Resources.%0aCost 4+%0aRequires Resources 4+.%0aCarried%0aIn Equipment Note, identify which items are typically “Carried.”%0a%0a[[#top | &#8593; back to top]]%0a%0aSanctioning%0aSee Sanctioning for assistance.%0a%0a[[#top | &#8593; back to top]]%0a%0aHouse Rules%0aSee House Rules for custom rules.%0a%0a[[#top | &#8593; back to top]]%0a%0aDirectory: Game Reference%0aBook Policy	House Rules	Character Creation	Sanctioning	Experience Guide	Code of Conduct	Site Policies And Practices%0aEdit - History - Print - Recent Changes - Search%0aPage last modified on April 16, 2017, at 12:19 PM%0aThe Storytelling System, Beast the Primordial, Changeling the Lost, Chronicles of Darkness, Demon the Descent, Mage the Awakening, Vampire the Requiem, and Werewolf the Forsaken ©2014-2016 CCP hf and published by Onyx Path Publishing.%0aProduced by Jeff Vandenberg. Layout and Design by Jill Arden ©2016
