 Backgrounds/Concepts%0a%3c Please be aware that the following backgrounds or concepts are not allowed:%0a%3c %0a%3c Anachronistic or over-the-top concepts. (Ninja, serial killer, Queen of England)%0a%3c Recreations of signature characters of any book, film or other popular fiction.%0a%3c Direct recreation of any actual person, living or dead.%0a%3c Characters already played by you or another person during WW5 or currently on another site. See Site Policies And Practices.%0a%3c Antagonist concepts (Loyalists, Pure, Seers, etc.)%0a%3c Backgrounds which include rape. See Site Policy.%0a%3c Notes%0a%3c This field is primarily to call out any bonus items gained from the purchase of other traits. Sanctioning staff members will use this section to complete your character sheet during sanctioning.%0a%3c %0a%3c [&#8593; back to top]%0a%3c %0a%3c Stats%0a%3c Attributes%0a%3c Unlike the RAW Character Creation, we do not limit Attribute point allocation at Character Creation to 5/4/3. All Attributes begin at 1 for free.%0a%3c %0a%3c Attribute 4+%0a%3c This must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a%3c Attribute 1%0a%3c This must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a%3c Skills%0a%3c Unlike the RAW Character Creation, we do not limit Skill point allocation at Character Creation to 11/7/4.%0a%3c %0a%3c Skill 4+%0a%3c This must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a%3c Occult Specialties%0a%3c This must be explained in Biography or Notes. Specialties in other Character Types represents significant “insider” knowledge and requires a detailed and fitting explanation.%0a%3c [&#8593; back to top]%0a%3c %0a%3c Traits%0a%3c NOTE%0a%3c Certain traits (abilities, merits, etc.) grant additional bonuses elsewhere such as a bonus specialty or +1 to an attribute. If your character is granted a bonus, make note of it in your NOTES section of the character sheet. During sanctioning, the staff member will use that list to update your character sheet. Example: Professional Training.%0a%3c Abilities%0a%3c All	%0a%3c Cost Breaks%0a%3c Merits and powers providing Experience cost breaks do not apply to character creation unless they explicitly say so.%0a%3c %0a%3c Changeling Only	%0a%3c Wyrd%0a%3c 3 must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a%3c 4+ is not allowed at Character Creation.%0a%3c Pledges%0a%3c This must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a%3c Non-Affinity Abilities%0a%3c Check the “NA” box for all Non-Affinity Contracts.%0a%3c Mage Only	%0a%3c Gnosis%0a%3c 3 must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a%3c 4+ is not allowed at Character Creation.%0a%3c Praxis%0a%3c Remember to record a number of free Praxes equal to the character’s Gnosis in Notes to be added to the sheet during sanctioning%0a%3c Arcana%0a%3c 4+ is not allowed at Character Creation.%0a%3c Vampire Only	%0a%3c Blood Potency%0a%3c 3 must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a%3c 4+ is not allowed at Character Creation.%0a%3c Non-Affinity Abilities%0a%3c Check the “NA” box for all Non-Affinity Disciplines.%0a%3c Werewolf Only	%0a%3c Primal Urge%0a%3c 3 must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a%3c 4+ is not allowed at Character Creation.%0a%3c Non-Affinity Abilities%0a%3c Check the “NA” box for all Non-Affinity Gifts.%0a%3c Wolf-Blooded Only	%0a%3c Tells%0a%3c Tells are capped at 4 total at creation, with those after the first purchased as a merit normally.%0a%3c The following Tells are only available at Character Creation as they are Tells present from birth:%0a%3c Moon Marked%0a%3c Second Skin%0a%3c Shadow Twin%0a%3c [&#8593; back to top]%0a%3c %0a%3c Merits%0a%3c All Merit purchases at Character Creation must meet the Prerequisites in the RAW. The following general Merit guidelines are applicable to all merits except where listed under the specific Merit type.%0a%3c %0a%3c Merit 4+%0a%3c This must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a%3c Scaled Merit 4+ without a listed pre-requisite%0a%3c Limited to 2 at Character Creation.%0a%3c Mortal Only	Per Hurt Locker, the following minor templates are available:%0a%3c Atariya%0a%3c Plain%0a%3c Lost Boys%0a%3c Psychic Vampires%0a%3c The first dot in the defining merit of the minor template is free.%0a%3c %0a%3c Supernatural Merits	Ghouls, Wolf-Blooded and Fae-Touched are not eligible for Supernatural Merits listed in Chronicles of Darkness.%0a%3c Wolf-Blooded Only	%0a%3c Raised By Wolves%0a%3c This merit is required for a character who is a part of one of the Families. Being part of a Family is not a prerequisite for taking the merit if the character was raised among other werewolves.%0a%3c [&#8593; back to top]%0a%3c %0a%3c Mental Merits%0a%3c Professional Training 2+%0a%3c Limited to 1 at Character Creation.%0a%3c Use the Notes section under Character Bio to identify the merit or skill benefits obtained by this merit, and the Sanctioning Staff will add them to your sheet during sanctioning.%0a%3c Select two applicable Asset Skills if your Profession is not listed in the RAW, and there is not a close approximation.%0a%3c Social Merits%0a%3c Allies, Contacts, Mentor%0a%3c This must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a%3c In the Merit Notes include the Sphere which the Allies, Contact or Mentor represents. As in: Contacts: (City Hall/Government) Mayor’s Office%0a%3c Mystery Cult Initiation%0a%3c A character may only have a total of 5 6 dots assigned to this merit(s). This must be explained in Biography or Notes.+}%0a%3c Initiation may be in a setting-created Cults or Groups (See ) or a player may create a new Cult. However, player-created Cults become part of the setting upon approval and may be co-opted into a primary setting cult and/or utilized for plot.%0a%3c Player-created Cults must be detailed in the Notes including an overview, cultist archetypes and rewards for each dot tier per the RAW guidelines. (CoD p.52)%0a%3c Use the Notes section under Character Bio to identify the merit or skill benefits obtained by this merit, and the Sanctioning Staff will add them to your sheet during sanctioning.%0a%3c Neighborhood 1+%0a%3c This is a House Ruled Merit. This must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a%3c Neighborhood 3+ not allowed as an individual purchase at Character Creation.%0a%3c Resources 3+%0a%3c This must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a%3c Safe Place 3+%0a%3c This must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a%3c Status%0a%3c This merit can only be purchased up to 2. All characters receive 1 free dot of status in one Faction-specific group (for example, a vampire may take 1 free dot of either Covenant or Clan status).%0a%3c The following Spheres are available for purchasing status:%0a%3c Arts and Society%0a%3c Business%0a%3c Crime%0a%3c Education%0a%3c Law and Order%0a%3c Media%0a%3c Medical%0a%3c Shadow Status in this Sphere cannot be purchased at Character Creation.%0a%3c Physical Merits%0a%3c Fighting Style 3+%0a%3c Limited to 1 at Character Creation.%0a%3c [&#8593; back to top]%0a%3c %0a%3c Influences%0a%3c Anchors%0a%3c For Virtue and Vice, Masque and Mein, Mask and Dirge, or Blood and Bone select the applicable choice from the Drop Down or enter a custom value.%0a%3c %0a%3c Touchstone%0a%3c For supernatural characters, this must be explained in Biography or Notes.%0a%3c Aspirations%0a%3c See Site Policies And Practices for Aspirations help.%0a%3c %0a%3c Short Term Aspiration%0a%3c Choose at least two short-term aspirations.%0a%3c Long term Aspiration%0a%3c Choose at least one long-term aspiration.%0a%3c Mage Only	%0a%3c Obsessions%0a%3c Choose at least one long-term obsession that is associated with your mystical life.%0a%3c Integrity and equivalents%0a%3c Mortal Only	%0a%3c Questionaire%0a%3c These questions need to be answered in addition to the Biography and Notes.%0a%3c For applicable characters	%0a%3c Identify Breaking Points%0a%3c %0a%3c Note:	%0a%3c You never have to make breaking point/detachment/etc rolls for things that happened before sanctioning (for example, a Vampire that has Cruac).%0a%3c %0a%3c [&#8593; back to top]%0a%3c %0a%3c Equipment%0a%3c Add any equipment plus applicable modifiers to your character sheet.%0a%3c %0a%3c Cost 1–3%0a%3c Some leeway is given for one Cost 3 item, 2 Cost 2 items or 3 Cost 1 items without adequate Resources.%0a%3c Cost 4+%0a%3c Requires Resources 4+.%0a%3c Carried%0a%3c In Equipment Note, identify which items are typically “Carried.”%0a%3c [&#8593; back to top]%0a%3c %0a%3c Sanctioning%0a%3c See Sanctioning for assistance.%0a%3c %0a%3c [&#8593; back to top]%0a%3c %0a%3c House Rules%0a%3c See House Rules for custom rules.%0a%3c %0a%3c [&#8593; back to top]%0a%3c %0a%3c Directory: Game Reference%0a%3c Book Policy	House Rules	Character Creation	Sanctioning	Experience Guide	Code of Conduct	Site Policies And Practices%0a%3c Edit - History - Print - Recent Changes - Search%0a%3c Page last modified on April 16, 2017, at 12:19 PM%0a%3c The Storytelling System, Beast the Primordial, Changeling the Lost, Chronicles of Darkness, Demon the Descent, Mage the Awakening, Vampire the Requiem, and Werewolf the Forsaken ©2014-2016 CCP hf and published by Onyx Path Publishing.%0a%3c Produced by Jeff Vandenberg. Layout and Design by Jill Arden ©2016%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
